description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a full time staff nurse to work within the Mental Health Rehabilitation and Recovery Service Group, Bridgend area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cefn Yr Afon is an eighteen bedded community rehabilitation and recovery unit that provides a step down service to patients from various inpatient and community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our philosophy is to provide a person centred service which maximises the person’s quality of life, promotes independence, and social inclusion whilst maintaining the focus on individual strengths, providing hope on the journey towards recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would be expected to assess, plan, facilitate and deliver care to all inpatients and to ensure that all aspects of their care is delivered to the highest possible standard. This includes working as part of a multidisciplinary team and liaising with a variety of professionals/agencies both in the community and within inpatient services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff work on a shift pattern which includes nights and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 15/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Beverley Francis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Unit Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: beverley.francis@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01656 763150/763151&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Beverley Francis, Unit Manager for further information.&lt;/p&gt;
